    73	## Reusable knowledge
    74	
    75	- The current AreaMatrix workflow should be explained as three distinct layers: `docs/` as SSOT, `workflow/` for version/planning lifecycle, and `tasks/prompts/**` as the approved live queue; `./task-loop` only executes the queue instead of making requirement decisions [Task 1]
    76	- A durable current-workflow chain is: `docs -> workflow/templates -> workflow/versions/v*/discussion -> middle-layer -> changes -> plans -> drafts -> queue -> promotion preview -> tasks/prompts/** -> ./task-loop run -> archive` [Task 1]
    77	- New `v*` versions must pass the discussion gate before `changes/`: `docs-discussion.md`, `middle-layer-discussion.md`, and `decisions.yaml`, with `allow_changes: true` and no unresolved blockers/open questions [Task 1][Task 2]
